radiographic_examinations.findings: Radiodense wire of left PICC terminates within the lower superior vena cava, and the tip of the catheter appears to extend approximately 1.8 cm below this level just above the junction of the superior vena cava and right atrium. The heart size is normal. Scattered interstitial opacities are present in the right lung as well as an ill-defined peripheral area of opacification at the right base, accompanied by small right effusion. The left lung is clear.
